document_type.description:
Classify this document into exactly one DocumentType. Choose the most specific match
based on the document's primary purpose and authoring context. When a document contains
content from multiple types (e.g., a discharge summary quoting endoscopy findings),
classify by the document's own type, not its quoted content.

GI_CLINIC_NOTE: outpatient GI/IBD visit note (physician, fellow, NP, PA); includes telehealth;
INPATIENT_PROGRESS_NOTE: daily inpatient progress note (attending, fellow, resident) during a hospital admission;
ENDOSCOPY_REPORT: formal procedure report for any luminal endoscopy (colonoscopy, EGD, capsule, pouchoscopy, etc.);
OPERATIVE_REPORT: formal surgical procedure report (colectomy, ileocecectomy, fistula repair, etc.);
PATHOLOGY_REPORT: surgical pathology or biopsy report on any GI specimen (endoscopic or resection);
DISCHARGE_SUMMARY: end-of-admission summary regardless of discharging service;
GENETICS_NOTE: genetics/genomics clinic note, genetic counseling note, or molecular genetics lab report;
NUTRITION_NOTE: dietitian or nutrition support note; includes EEN/PEN therapy plans;
SUBSPECIALTY_CONSULT_NOTE: formal consult note from a non-GI subspecialty (rheumatology, ophthalmology, dermatology, immunology, etc.);
RADIOLOGY_REPORT: imaging report (MRE, CT, ultrasound, X-ray, nuclear medicine);
PEDIATRIC_SURGERY_CONSULT_NOTE: pediatric surgery consult note that does not describe a completed procedure;
INFUSION_OR_PHARMACY_RECORD: infusion center administration record, pharmacy dispensing record, or prior authorization document;
TRANSFER_OR_TRANSITION_NOTE: transition-of-care summary, transfer note, referral letter, or outside-records summary;
OTHER: document is identifiable but does not match any type above;
UNKNOWN: document type cannot be determined from available content; use only as a last resort.
